Privacy Policy for Lazy Bookmark

Lazy Bookmark does not collect, store, transmit, or share any personal data.

Permissions used:
1. "bookmarks" – This permission is required to read the user's existing bookmarks for the purpose of displaying search results inside the extension. No bookmark data is sent outside the user's browser.
2. "storage" – This permission is used only to store local usage frequency data to improve search ranking. This data stays entirely on the user's device and is never transmitted elsewhere.

Lazy Bookmark does not use analytics, tracking, advertising, cookies, user profiling, or any third-party data services.

No personal information is collected, shared, or processed.

If you have questions about this privacy policy, you may contact the developer through the email listed in the Chrome Web Store developer profile.
